
                                            It’s believed the Malmesbury man swallowed 500 grams of cocaine before he made the trip of Luanda in Angola to Cape Town.
                                         CAPE TOWN - The case against a 39-year-old suspected drug mule was heard in the Bellville Magistrates Court on Wednesday after his arrest on Monday at the Cape Town International Airport. It’s believed the Malmesbury man swallowed 500 grams of cocaine before he made the trip of Luanda in Angola to Cape Town. The Hawk’s Lloyd Ramovha said: “The suspect was identified and taken to a nearby medical facility for an x-ray. This revealed foreign objects in his abdomen. The objects were later identified as 25 bullets of cocaine, weighing about 500 grams.”